      "explained": "The two defining properties of similarity — equal corresponding angles and constant ratios of corresponding sides — explain why the passport photo looks identical at two different sizes: the photographer's software applied one linear scale factor (3) to every length, preserving all angles and keeping all side ratios equal. When only width is scaled (distorted photo), the ratio condition is violated and the image loses its shape."
