      "keyInquiry": "How do we identify and use similar figures in day-to-day situations?",
      "purposeInStoryline": "In Lessons 1–4, learners established WHAT similarity looks like (equal angles, proportional sides) and gathered evidence from the passport photo puzzle. In this Explain lesson (Lesson 5), learners now formalise the mechanism — the Linear Scale Factor — that the photographer's software used to resize the image. They move from describing similarity to calculating with it, directly answering the first part of the driving question: 'What is the mathematics that makes this possible?'",
