        "teacherMoves": "PART A: Distribute model-answer strips. Say: 'You are marking your partner's thinking — be precise and be kind. Write one sentence for every red cross explaining what went wrong.' Give 10 minutes. PART B: Write 3 anonymous errors on the board, e.g., Error 1: 'Area of real roof = 450 × 25 = 11 250 cm²' (used LSF, not LSF²). Error 2: 'Volume of large tank = 1 200 × 3 = 3 600 litres' (used LSF, not LSF³). Error 3: 'LSF of second map = 5 000 000 ÷ 2 500 000 = 2' (correct value but inverted interpretation). For each error say: 'Talk to your partner — what mistake was made and what is the correct approach? 2 minutes.' Allow 15 seconds wait time after pairs stop talking. Cold-call 3 different learners per error (9 cold-calls total). After each: 'Does anyone want to add to or challenge that explanation?' PART C: Project passport photo. Say: 'You have been building to this moment since Lesson 1. Write your Final Explanation now — 4 to 6 sentences. Use ALL five terms on the board: LSF, ASF, VSF, similar figures, angle preservation. You have 5 minutes.' Circulate and read over shoulders — do not correct yet.",
