        "teacherMoves": "Hand out two sticky notes per learner. Say: 'Yellow note — write the two formulas that complete our DQB. Blue note — write one question this unit has opened up for you, not answered.' Give 3 minutes. Invite all learners to the DQB simultaneously to post notes. Then stand at the DQB and say: 'Let's read our journey.' Read aloud 3 questions from Lesson 1's 'What We Wonder' column and the corresponding answers now in 'What We Know.' Narrate: 'In Lesson 1 you asked why the face doesn't distort. Today you can answer that yourself.' Cold-call 2 learners: 'In one sentence — why does the face NOT distort when LSF is applied equally to both dimensions?' Allow 10 seconds wait time. Read 4–5 blue sticky notes aloud and say: 'These questions belong to the next chapter of your mathematical life.'",
